#### 1. üìú Find the talon js file

Go to [This url](https://www.epicgames.com/id/login), launch the dev console, and under the ***"Sources"*** tabs. You will find a `talon.js` file.

![Footer](./img/1.png)

#### 2. ü™Å Deobfuscate the talon js file

You will see that `talon.js` is obfuscated. To deobfuscate it, go on [this url](https://obf-io.deobfuscate.io/) and do the same shit that on the pic.

![Footer](./img/2.png)

---

#### 3. üß≤ Find important function

To find the important function for getting xal json and xal encrypted, you will need the perfect IDE such as VSCode (Visual Studio Code). Then make a search in the `talon.js` file (opened in vscode) with some keywords like:

- fingerprint
- fp
- hash
- encrypt
- xal
- talon

![Footer](./img/3.png)

Like the picture, you can find the perfect function.

*PS: I tested the talon code in the web folder.*
